    {
      "question": "When $f(x) = x^3 - 3x^2 + 5x - 3$ is divided by $g(x) = x^2 - 2$, the quotient $q(x)$ is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "options": [
        "(A) $x - 3$",
        "(B) $x - 3$ with remainder $7x - 9$",
        "(C) $x^2 - 3$",
        "(D) $x + 3$"
      ],
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Divide $x^3$ by $x^2$ to get $x$.",
          "Multiply $x(x^2 - 2) = x^3 - 2x$.",
          "Subtract $(x^3 - 3x^2 + 5x - 3) - (x^3 - 2x) = -3x^2 + 7x - 3$.",
          "Divide $-3x^2$ by $x^2$ to get $-3$.",
          "The quotient is $x - 3$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$(x^3 - 3x^2 + 5x - 3) = (x^2 - 2)(x - 3) + (7x - 9)$"
      },
      "topic": "Polynomials",
