    {
      "question": "A polynomial $p(x)$ of degree $3$ is divided by $(x^2 - 1)$ resulting in a quotient $(x - 1)$ and a remainder $(2x + 3)$. Find the polynomial $p(x)$.",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "options": [
        "(A) $x^3 - x^2 + x + 2$",
        "(B) $x^3 + x^2 + x + 2$",
        "(C) $x^3 - x^2 - x + 2$",
        "(D) $x^3 + x^2 - x + 2$"
      ],
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use $p(x) = g(x)q(x) + r(x)$.",
          "Given $g(x) = x^2 - 1$, $q(x) = x - 1$, $r(x) = 2x + 3$.",
          "Expand $(x^2 - 1)(x - 1) = x^3 - x^2 - x + 1$.",
          "Add the remainder: $(x^3 - x^2 - x + 1) + (2x + 3) = x^3 - x^2 + x + 4$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$p(x) = (x^2 - 1)(x - 1) + 2x + 3 = x^3 - x^2 - x + 1 + 2x + 3 = x^3 - x^2 + x + 4$"
      },
